{"id":4517,"date":"2021-12-30T09:08:29","date_gmt":"2021-12-30T09:08:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/?p=4517"},"modified":"2022-04-18T21:47:52","modified_gmt":"2022-04-18T21:47:52","slug":"highbury-park-seasons","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/highbury-park-seasons\/","title":{"rendered":"Highbury Park: all we need to know is here"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>I started taking photos of Highbury Park during the 2020 lockdown, as, like many, walking became my exercise, my social life and my prayer. This image is of what I now call <a href=\"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/place\/\">Cathedral Avenue<\/a> &#8211; a row of lime trees that remind me of a nave.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a very simple idea &#8211; taking photographs from the same spot through the seasons (and not an original one either). But I have found it more profound than I had anticipated.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-scaled.jpg\" rel=\"lightbox[4517]\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1249\" src=\"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"A beautiful avenue of lime trees in Highbury Park, Birmingham taken in spring, summer, autumn and winter.\" class=\"wp-image-4518\" srcset=\"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-300x146.jpg 300w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-700x341.jpg 700w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-768x375.jpg 768w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-1536x749.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-2048x999.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-800x390.jpg 800w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-1200x585.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Highbury-Park-composite-1400x683.jpg 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><\/a><figcaption>Cathedral Avenue in Highbury Park, Birmingham<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It reminds me that life is always changing. To live well is therefore to allow life to flow through you like a river, rather than try to hold onto the good times as though they can last. It teaches me that death and loss are as much a part of life as buds and blossom.  It shows me that winter is as beautiful as summer and autumn as lovely as spring. So when I go through my times of grief &#8211; as I most surely have and most surely will again &#8211; I can welcome them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, I think this is all we need to know, just this &#8211; just what the trees through the seasons can tell us. If we understood this deeply, we would be most fully alive.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I started taking photos of Highbury Park during the 2020 lockdown, as, like many, walking became my exercise, my social life and my prayer. This image is of what I now call Cathedral Avenue &#8211; a row of lime trees that remind me of a nave.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":4640,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[254,8],"tags":[181],"class_list":["post-4517","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-green","category-prayer","tag-soul"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4517"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/pos